00:08:58.710 --> 00:09:02.740
Okay. So here we
have a floor plan.

00:09:02.740 --> 00:09:06.350
This is a configuration
that was done by Bill Allen

00:09:06.350 --> 00:09:09.640
and his seminal work
on the Capitol.

00:09:09.640 --> 00:09:13.850
So, again, this is that west
Senate front where the Library

00:09:13.850 --> 00:09:17.270
of Congress was located,
the Clerk of the House,

00:09:17.270 --> 00:09:19.530
and so forth, the
Senate gallery level,

00:09:19.530 --> 00:09:20.830
[inaudible] hall, et cetera.

00:09:20.830 --> 00:09:22.460
Now, again, it is hard

00:09:22.460 --> 00:09:24.390
to overstate the
importance of these rooms.

00:09:24.390 --> 00:09:27.720
First of all, the House of
Representatives first met here,

00:09:27.720 --> 00:09:31.230
gaveled to order, on
November the 17th 1800

00:09:31.230 --> 00:09:34.250
by Theodore Sedgwick
of Massachusetts.

00:09:34.250 --> 00:09:36.160
The Library of Congress
was established there.

00:09:36.160 --> 00:09:39.420
The election of 1800,
the very famous election

00:09:39.420 --> 00:09:42.590
of Thomas Jefferson as
president, was decided.

00:09:42.590 --> 00:09:44.770
Remember that election
was thrown

00:09:44.770 --> 00:09:46.070
to the House of Representatives.

00:09:46.070 --> 00:09:48.530
So these rooms not only home
to the Library of Congress,

00:09:48.530 --> 00:09:51.410
but many, many important
historical events

00:09:51.410 --> 00:09:52.710
happened there.

00:09:52.710 --> 00:09:54.190
And also the Supreme Court

00:09:54.190 --> 00:09:57.870
and the Senate shared
this space as well.

