00:10:35.150 --> 00:10:39.750
Next, we have Benjamin
Latrobe becomes architect

00:10:39.750 --> 00:10:44.310
of the Capitol, indeed
before the fire.

00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:49.070
Benjamin Latrobe an absolute
genius architect, engineer,

00:10:49.070 --> 00:10:50.970
artist, absolutely
brilliant man.

00:10:50.970 --> 00:10:53.320
He was born in Yorkshire,
England.

00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:55.680
One of the first formally
trained architects

00:10:55.680 --> 00:10:57.020
in the United States.

00:10:57.020 --> 00:10:59.010
He was also a painter,
by the way.

00:10:59.010 --> 00:11:02.840
He traveled widely throughout
Europe, mastered German, French,

00:11:02.840 --> 00:11:04.940
ancient and modern
Greek, and Latin.

00:11:04.940 --> 00:11:09.120
He emigrated to the U.S.
in 1796, designed the Bank

00:11:09.120 --> 00:11:12.780
of Pennsylvania, as you
see here, the first example

00:11:12.780 --> 00:11:15.710
of Greek Revival architecture
in the United States.

00:11:15.710 --> 00:11:18.420
He also designed the
Baltimore Basilica,

00:11:18.420 --> 00:11:21.490
the first Roman Catholic
cathedral in the United States.

00:11:21.490 --> 00:11:24.980
You can see similarities
with Jefferson--

00:11:24.980 --> 00:11:27.940
that education, that
travel in Europe.

00:11:27.940 --> 00:11:29.240
All of those things.

00:11:29.240 --> 00:11:30.540
You just know immediately

00:11:30.540 --> 00:11:32.010
that these two are
going to become friends.

00:11:32.010 --> 00:11:34.890
And, indeed, their
partnership lives with us today.

00:11:34.890 --> 00:11:38.250
Their partnership, as we
will see, affects a lot

00:11:38.250 --> 00:11:41.330
of the decisions that went into
the Thomas Jefferson Building.

00:11:41.330 --> 00:11:46.100
He worked on the Capitol from
1803 until the war of 1812,

00:11:46.100 --> 00:11:50.050
and then again starting in 1815.

00:11:50.050 --> 00:11:53.570
Other notable buildings
by Latrobe

00:11:53.570 --> 00:11:57.050
in our area include St.
John's Episcopal Church

00:11:57.050 --> 00:12:01.590
on Lafayette Square, St. Paul's
in my hometown of Alexandria,

00:12:01.590 --> 00:12:03.310
of course, the Baltimore
Basilica,

00:12:03.310 --> 00:12:04.610
which I just referenced.

00:12:04.610 --> 00:12:07.200
This is widely regarded

00:12:07.200 --> 00:12:09.540
as his real masterpiece
in this country.

00:12:09.540 --> 00:12:13.810
And then also I love the
gate to the Navy Yard,

00:12:13.810 --> 00:12:17.260
right down the street from us.

00:12:17.260 --> 00:12:18.790
Next. All right.

00:12:18.790 --> 00:12:21.900
So this is the picture,
